## 3. What Is an API?

API means:

```text
Application Programming Interface
```

An API defines how one software system communicates with another.

Examples:

* A weather application requesting forecast data
* A mobile application sending login information
* A chatbot sending a prompt to an AI model
* A website requesting product prices
* A machine-learning service returning predictions

A simple API interaction:

```text
Client
  |
  | Request
  v
Server
  |
  | Response
  v
Client
```

The client asks for something.

The server processes the request and returns a response.

---

## 4. What Is HTTP?

HTTP is a communication protocol used by web applications and APIs.

A request normally contains:

```text
Method
URL
Headers
Query parameters
Optional body
```

A response normally contains:

```text
Status code
Headers
Response body
```

Example:

```text
GET /students/42
```

Response:

```json
{
  "id": 42,
  "name": "Ali",
  "score": 85
}
```

---

## 5. API Endpoint

An endpoint is a URL representing an API resource or operation.

Example structure:

```text
https://api.example.com/v1/students
```

Parts:

```text
https://              Protocol
api.example.com       Domain
/v1                   API version
/students             Resource
```

Specific student:

```text
https://api.example.com/v1/students/42
```

