## 6. Common HTTP Methods

### GET

Retrieves data.

```text
GET /students
GET /students/42
```

### POST

Creates data or submits work.

```text
POST /predictions
POST /students
```

### PUT

Usually replaces a complete resource.

```text
PUT /students/42
```

### PATCH

Updates part of a resource.

```text
PATCH /students/42
```

### DELETE

Removes a resource.

```text
DELETE /students/42
```

Summary:

| Method | Typical purpose   |
| ------ | ----------------- |
| GET    | Read              |
| POST   | Create or execute |
| PUT    | Replace           |
| PATCH  | Partially update  |
| DELETE | Remove            |

---

## 7. HTTP Status Codes

Status codes indicate the result of a request.

### Success

```text
200 OK
201 Created
204 No Content
```

### Client Errors

```text
400 Bad Request
401 Unauthorized
403 Forbidden
404 Not Found
409 Conflict
422 Unprocessable Content
429 Too Many Requests
```

### Server Errors

```text
500 Internal Server Error
502 Bad Gateway
503 Service Unavailable
504 Gateway Timeout
```

Status-code groups:

```text
2xx → Success
4xx → Client-side problem
5xx → Server-side problem
```

A `200` response does not guarantee that the returned data is logically correct. The response structure must still be validated.

