## 11. Query Parameters

Query parameters modify or filter a request.

Example URL:

```text
/students?course=AI&minimum_score=80
```

Python:

```python
params = {
    "course": "AI",
    "minimum_score": 80,
}

response = requests.get(
    "https://api.example.com/v1/students",
    params=params,
    timeout=10,
)
```

Requests converts the dictionary into a query string.

This is safer than manually concatenating strings.

