## 12. Request Headers

Headers provide request metadata.

```python
headers = {
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "User-Agent": "StudentAnalytics/1.0",
}

response = requests.get(
    "https://api.example.com/v1/students",
    headers=headers,
    timeout=10,
)
```

Common headers:

```text
Accept
Content-Type
Authorization
User-Agent
```

`Accept` describes the response format the client expects.

`Content-Type` describes the body format being sent.

