## 16. Timeouts

This is unsafe:

```python
requests.get(url)
```

The request may wait for a long time.

Use:

```python
requests.get(
    url,
    timeout=10,
)
```

You can separate connection and reading timeouts:

```python
requests.get(
    url,
    timeout=(3, 10),
)
```

Meaning:

```text
3 seconds  → Connection timeout
10 seconds → Response-read timeout
```

Timeouts are essential in production systems.

